  <chunk id="155cca2a90a5430ac391b46983efa4c13f193289.c2" text="Results: WTA successfully amplified cDNA from a panel of RNA viruses representing the diversity of ribovirus genome sizes. We amplified a range of genome copy numbers from 15 to 4 × 10 7 using WTA, which yielded quantities of amplified DNA as high as 1.2 μg/μl or 10 10 target copies. The amplification factor varied between 10 9 and 10 6 . We also demonstrated that co-amplification occurred when viral RNA was mixed with bacterial DNA.">
